div.font: Round 0: Initially, an object is put on node 4, and it is ready for peering.

div.style: font-size: 40px
font-size: 40px
div.font: Round 1: Node 8 is chosen randomly, and the object is copied from node 4 to node 8. At the end of this round, Node 4 and 8 become peering ready.

div.style: font-size: 40px
font-size: 40px
div.font: Round 2: Another two nodes, 3 and 11, are chosen randomly, and they fetch data from node 8 and node 4 respectively. Notice that, at the end of this round, node 4 goes into a peering done statue, and no more data transmission from this node will happen in the following rounds.

div.style: font-size: 40px
font-size: 40px
div.font: Round 3: Things are done in the same manner. Another three nodes become peering ready and node 8 becomes peering done.

div.style: font-size: 40px
font-size: 40px
div.font: Round 4: Finally, the object has spread to all nodes.

div.style: font-size: 40px
font-size: 40px
div.font: The diagram shown above is simplified for ease of illustration. There is no concept of the round. Every time a node has received the data, it begins sending data to the remaining nodes. The maximum number of nodes for that node has to send to is defined as fanout(2, in this example), which is configurable.
